Do you have a special childhood memory from the weekends?
We were a warm and united family.
On Friday at noon, my mother would prepare a pile of schnitzels, bring hummus and pita from the market, and burn eggplants for a tahini salad.
Then we would go to Aunt Hannah's in Yad Eliyahu, or as she used to say, Yad Eliyke, and she would make lynchings.
Since only I didn't like raisins, she would make me some without raisins.
She saw me, the youngest of the brothers, and took care of me.
On Saturdays we would do a tour with my father in the port of Jaffa, and he would show us where he and his twin brother, Grisha, came to Israel with nothing. "
