A horrific mistake occurred at the Wolfson Government Hospital in Holon, when during an operation the doctor ruptured the patient's heart, leading to his tragic death.
The surgery on the 83-year-old lung cancer patient was performed on April 19.
It was the first surgery performed by Dr. Faras Abu Akar at the hospital, after he was appointed director of the thoracic surgery unit at Wolfson.
During the operation, which was designed to drain the area surrounding the patient's heart, the surgeon accidentally caused a large rupture in the heart, which led to severe bleeding and caused the patient's death.
But the unusual complication opened a Pandora's box, which raised difficult questions regarding the management of the hospital.
The director of the oncology institute and chairman of the doctors' committee, Dr. Ronen Brenner, demanded an investigation of the affair in a letter he sent to the hospital's director, Dr. Anat Engel.
